cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper deals with explaining the predictions of image classifiers, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach that uses decision trees, which is a popular machine learning (ML) technique. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (ML) and cs.AI (AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of explainability in AI, which could make it relevant to cs.CL (natural language processing and computational linguistics) and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
